The big city is gone.

01:02:29.280 --> 01:02:33.270
Here is in our environment
a non-polluting environment.

01:02:33.270 --> 01:02:40.980
The landscape is vital and
indulges farming and landscape

01:02:40.980 --> 01:02:42.810
for beauty's sake.

01:02:42.810 --> 01:02:44.370
Here's a river.

01:02:44.370 --> 01:02:46.985
There's traditional
methods of power.

01:02:46.985 --> 01:02:49.830
There are new methods of power.

01:02:49.830 --> 01:02:54.030
There's a windmill on the
top, on the hill on the right.

01:02:58.950 --> 01:03:00.930
This is the antidote to London.

01:03:00.930 --> 01:03:04.500
This is William Morris'
version of what the world would

01:03:04.500 --> 01:03:10.000
be like if you could substitute
London for it, a bad choice,

01:03:10.000 --> 01:03:10.540
I believe.

01:03:10.540 --> 01:03:11.040
Next.

01:03:13.500 --> 01:03:20.550
Victor Considerant and
Charles Fourier's phalanstere,

01:03:20.550 --> 01:03:24.020
an extraordinary
sensibility that this

01:03:24.020 --> 01:03:32.450
is using the same architectural
forms as used in--

01:03:32.450 --> 01:03:34.220
under the auspices of royalty.

01:03:37.490 --> 01:03:40.310
What is it about
behaving differently

01:03:40.310 --> 01:03:44.450
that will succeed if you
put it into a palace?

01:03:49.180 --> 01:03:52.750
There's something about
this dream and fear story.

01:03:52.750 --> 01:03:55.630
If I dream too much, I
need to supply myself

01:03:55.630 --> 01:03:59.050
with nourishment, security.

01:03:59.050 --> 01:04:02.200
And maybe architecture
of a certain kind

01:04:02.200 --> 01:04:07.775
produces security when
you dream too far.

01:04:07.775 --> 01:04:08.275
Next.

01:04:12.180 --> 01:04:17.790
Rue interieure on the left,
pretty modest invention.

01:04:17.790 --> 01:04:21.490
Courtland's wife made
so much fuss about it.

01:04:21.490 --> 01:04:26.340
And this on the right
is the interior version

01:04:26.340 --> 01:04:29.850
of the phalanstere
called the familistere

01:04:29.850 --> 01:04:34.415
by Jean [? Godin-- ?] next--

01:04:34.415 --> 01:04:36.595
[INAUDIBLE] Guise in France.

01:04:36.595 --> 01:04:37.095
Next.

01:04:39.940 --> 01:04:45.910
And this preoccupation
with the establishment

01:04:45.910 --> 01:04:50.980
of the child's world as
outside of the family, these

01:04:50.980 --> 01:04:58.960
are children in Robert
Owen and [INAUDIBLE] being

01:04:58.960 --> 01:05:04.790
looked after by not the parents,
but by trained educators.

01:05:07.730 --> 01:05:12.020
There's something about
the next generation

01:05:12.020 --> 01:05:19.255
of people being
uncontaminated by the effect

01:05:19.255 --> 01:05:20.500
of the appearance.

01:05:23.280 --> 01:05:29.010
The kibbutz movement in Israel
went through great crisis

01:05:29.010 --> 01:05:33.270
around the extremes
of this attention

01:05:33.270 --> 01:05:35.845
to the education of children.

01:05:35.845 --> 01:05:36.345
Next.

01:05:40.760 --> 01:05:46.910
The one environment which
maintains the physical form

01:05:46.910 --> 01:05:50.340
as an absolute is
the Shaker movement.

01:05:50.340 --> 01:05:54.440
This is a Shaker settlement
in Hancock, Massachusetts.

01:05:54.440 --> 01:05:58.940
On the right are just
indications of the precision

01:05:58.940 --> 01:06:01.290
of the environment.

01:06:01.290 --> 01:06:05.390
There is no doubt as to
where you hang your hat.

01:06:05.390 --> 01:06:07.700
Everybody will
wear the same hat.

01:06:07.700 --> 01:06:10.430
Everybody will wear
the same clothes.

01:06:10.430 --> 01:06:13.810
The broom will hang in the
right position next to a door.

01:06:17.390 --> 01:06:17.890
Next.

01:06:21.350 --> 01:06:31.580
The American scene Humphrey
Noyes and his Oneida community,

01:06:31.580 --> 01:06:35.890
also based on some
version of sexuality.

01:06:35.890 --> 01:06:38.780
The Rappites, the
Bethel Rappites,

01:06:38.780 --> 01:06:42.300
the great movement
across this country.

01:06:42.300 --> 01:06:44.275
The Mormon-- next--

01:06:48.480 --> 01:06:52.350
the Mormon spatial
program, they lay out

01:06:52.350 --> 01:06:54.480
one square mile of territory.

01:06:59.520 --> 01:07:03.060
Their houses will be
built of stone and brick

01:07:03.060 --> 01:07:06.450
according to the
choice of the owner.

01:07:06.450 --> 01:07:12.150
But the layout often alternates
the direction of the plot line

01:07:12.150 --> 01:07:14.760
horizontally or vertically.

01:07:14.760 --> 01:07:17.160
There's some theory about
that which I don't quite

01:07:17.160 --> 01:07:18.055
understand myself.

01:07:20.940 --> 01:07:23.670
Can you imagine why
it would be better

01:07:23.670 --> 01:07:29.880
to have houses facing
the side of other houses?

01:07:29.880 --> 01:07:32.260
I don't know quite.

01:07:32.260 --> 01:07:34.890
I never quite figured this out.

01:07:34.890 --> 01:07:37.680
But then I'm not a great
reader of Mormonism.

01:07:40.320 --> 01:07:45.240
The Mormonic communal
activity in California,

01:07:45.240 --> 01:07:52.350
here theosophist community
acting out Aeschylus,

01:07:52.350 --> 01:07:55.740
part of the Greeks'
tragedy, a kind

01:07:55.740 --> 01:07:59.440
of freer version of
the Mormon program.

01:07:59.440 --> 01:07:59.940
Next.

01:08:03.250 --> 01:08:09.370
Fountain Grove, how
can I explain this?

01:08:09.370 --> 01:08:10.090
I can't.

01:08:10.090 --> 01:08:12.550
It's just wonderful.

01:08:12.550 --> 01:08:17.920
It's just a drawing for a
developer, the idea of what

01:08:17.920 --> 01:08:20.020
would attract people
if they came to live

01:08:20.020 --> 01:08:23.170
in a different environment.

01:08:23.170 --> 01:08:25.630
Unique versus
replicable plans is

01:08:25.630 --> 01:08:29.157
the text underneath
all of the [INAUDIBLE]..

01:08:31.970 --> 01:08:37.680
I could live here, I suppose,
if nobody else was there,

01:08:37.680 --> 01:08:41.569
if I had the whole thing.

01:08:41.569 --> 01:08:42.725
I'd have my own religion.

01:08:47.660 --> 01:08:48.609
Next please.

01:08:51.240 --> 01:08:59.600
Another Llano del Rio
intentional community.

01:08:59.600 --> 01:09:03.709
I think one should look at Drop
City rather than these, Drop

01:09:03.709 --> 01:09:13.380
City, which is somewhere
between the counterculture

01:09:13.380 --> 01:09:18.330
of California and cyber
culture of the internet.

01:09:18.330 --> 01:09:20.845
It's perhaps more interesting
to look at than these.

01:09:20.845 --> 01:09:21.345
Next.

01:09:25.170 --> 01:09:32.060
Now the industrial
town, [? Kronenburg, ?]

01:09:32.060 --> 01:09:41.550
the Krupp family and
Titus Salt, Titus Salt,

01:09:41.550 --> 01:09:48.920
Saltaire on the
right, distinguishing

01:09:48.920 --> 01:09:51.380
between the works
and the housing

01:09:51.380 --> 01:09:54.170
as two separate components.

01:09:54.170 --> 01:10:01.130
Not making use of the river as
a great amenity on the left.

01:10:01.130 --> 01:10:06.420
Titus Salt bought the Crystal
Palace, but it burnt down.

01:10:06.420 --> 01:10:06.920
Next.

01:10:10.420 --> 01:10:17.110
Port Sunlight by
the Lever brothers

01:10:17.110 --> 01:10:20.980
taking some of the Garden
City ideas of landscaping.

01:10:20.980 --> 01:10:26.020
This looks and feels like
a different kind of world

01:10:26.020 --> 01:10:28.620
than the world of Pullman.

01:10:28.620 --> 01:10:29.120
Next.

01:10:32.190 --> 01:10:36.600
And a number of
strange examples,

01:10:36.600 --> 01:10:39.570
that happy colony on
the left is by a man

01:10:39.570 --> 01:10:42.540
called Pemberton in
New Zealand in which

01:10:42.540 --> 01:10:49.380
the center of the environment
could be farms, model farms.

01:10:49.380 --> 01:10:52.800
And there would be four
colleges surrounding them.

01:10:52.800 --> 01:10:57.040
God alone knows what the world
of colleges and model farms

01:10:57.040 --> 01:10:58.580
has to do with reality.

01:10:58.580 --> 01:10:59.685
But still.

01:10:59.685 --> 01:11:06.360
Here is another
diversion on the right.

01:11:06.360 --> 01:11:10.850
I think it's in
Brazil from the 1970s.

01:11:10.850 --> 01:11:14.100
And it has a model
farm in the center

01:11:14.100 --> 01:11:18.270
and then housing just
distributed itself outwards.

01:11:18.270 --> 01:11:22.110
What is interesting
is the variation

01:11:22.110 --> 01:11:26.775
of the circular system from the
pervasive grid shown outside.

01:11:29.730 --> 01:11:32.520
What is it about
a model farm which

01:11:32.520 --> 01:11:37.130
centers a good environment?

01:11:37.130 --> 01:11:40.800
I suppose it's basically
from an agricultural world.

01:11:40.800 --> 01:11:41.300
Next.

01:11:44.050 --> 01:11:48.370
You see the town of Nahalal
on the left by the architect

01:11:48.370 --> 01:11:52.880
Richard Kauffmann, 1924, I
think where, again, there

01:11:52.880 --> 01:11:56.380
is a central, a central
impulse to create

01:11:56.380 --> 01:11:58.360
a central proposition.

01:11:58.360 --> 01:12:01.630
And radiating out from
it, it's almost as

01:12:01.630 --> 01:12:03.400
if the center is inviolate.

01:12:03.400 --> 01:12:06.290
The center has to be held.

01:12:06.290 --> 01:12:09.760
What's the poem by Yeats?

01:12:09.760 --> 01:12:11.245
"The center holds true."

01:12:15.510 --> 01:12:16.855
Some of you should know poetry.

01:12:19.790 --> 01:12:22.200
Yeats is a great poet.

01:12:22.200 --> 01:12:26.000
"The world falls apart, the
center holds, but the--"

01:12:26.000 --> 01:12:29.020
something distributes.

01:12:29.020 --> 01:12:34.460
Anyway, this is almost
primeval preoccupation

01:12:34.460 --> 01:12:35.570
with centeredness.

01:12:35.570 --> 01:12:39.860
We remember [INAUDIBLE],,
this phenomenon

01:12:39.860 --> 01:12:46.820
of the center in the pre-modern
or in the archaic environment.

01:12:46.820 --> 01:12:51.170
Here is a project by the French
group called [? Commonaut. ?]

01:12:51.170 --> 01:12:57.470
Again, the center is what is
the most valuable preoccupation.

01:12:57.470 --> 01:13:00.560
What happens around the
center just drifts off.

01:13:00.560 --> 01:13:02.700
Now [INAUDIBLE] does the same.

01:13:02.700 --> 01:13:03.200
Next.

01:13:05.760 --> 01:13:07.890
This is Tony Garnier.

01:13:07.890 --> 01:13:11.280
Look at the extraordinary
depiction of the works.

01:13:11.280 --> 01:13:13.815
The works is almost more
beautiful than the housing.

01:13:17.490 --> 01:13:24.400
The river is maintained as an
important production source.

01:13:24.400 --> 01:13:31.360
The ships are managed within
the realm of architecture.

01:13:34.660 --> 01:13:41.310
The works are all
along the river.

01:13:41.310 --> 01:13:47.580
On the upper left is the
housing, the linear housing.

01:13:47.580 --> 01:13:50.190
The hill which is
behind the housing

01:13:50.190 --> 01:13:54.270
has the heliotherapy
center in it.

01:13:54.270 --> 01:13:58.420
And the communal facilities
are in the black on the right.

01:13:58.420 --> 01:13:58.920
Next.

01:14:03.020 --> 01:14:06.530
The heliotherapy
center on the right.

01:14:06.530 --> 01:14:09.680
On the left, the all
communal auditorium,

01:14:09.680 --> 01:14:12.740
all shaped according to
a particular concrete

01:14:12.740 --> 01:14:13.365
architecture.

01:14:13.365 --> 01:14:13.865
Next.

01:14:17.820 --> 01:14:20.130
The house, the housing
environment, this

01:14:20.130 --> 01:14:26.640
is such a far reach
from Lever or Pullman

01:14:26.640 --> 01:14:31.440
or Krupp or people of that kind.

01:14:31.440 --> 01:14:36.000
This is almost the
interior of a Roman casa.

01:14:36.000 --> 01:14:41.220
The workers, this Renault
automobile factory worker's

01:14:41.220 --> 01:14:49.390
wife is seen doing a toilet in
this extraordinary environment.

01:14:49.390 --> 01:14:52.300
Of course, these are dreams.

01:14:52.300 --> 01:14:52.800
Next.

01:14:56.520 --> 01:15:02.110
Oak Park, Frank Lloyd
Wright's middle landscape.

01:15:02.110 --> 01:15:06.120
He built 15 houses there
and the Unity Church,

01:15:06.120 --> 01:15:08.460
one of his great buildings.

01:15:08.460 --> 01:15:12.450
Here is Broadacres, the
plan of Broadacre City,

01:15:12.450 --> 01:15:17.460
Broadacre City, which is a
very small piece of the built

01:15:17.460 --> 01:15:18.820
environment.

01:15:18.820 --> 01:15:24.810
I think its population is
something like 25,000, if that.

01:15:24.810 --> 01:15:29.400
Here the students
[INAUDIBLE] looking

01:15:29.400 --> 01:15:31.870
at the project in Arizona.

01:15:31.870 --> 01:15:32.370
Next.

01:15:35.740 --> 01:15:44.100
The plan is a rather
simple plan, the auditorium

01:15:44.100 --> 01:15:53.865
and cultural facilities, a
kind of environment which--

01:15:58.380 --> 01:16:03.150
in which the landscape is
a very important feature.

01:16:03.150 --> 01:16:08.640
There are lots of
facilities such as open air

01:16:08.640 --> 01:16:11.040
stalls for selling goods.

01:16:14.190 --> 01:16:18.260
The automobile
population is not fixed,

01:16:18.260 --> 01:16:21.870
but everybody who wants an
automobile can have one.

01:16:21.870 --> 01:16:26.100
This peculiar
perspective on the right

01:16:26.100 --> 01:16:29.940
indicates some kind of
alternative movement system.

01:16:33.060 --> 01:16:36.510
The technology of the
automobile has suddenly changed

01:16:36.510 --> 01:16:38.010
or it looks as to be changed.

01:16:38.010 --> 01:16:45.590
Looks as though it's
got telephone dialing

01:16:45.590 --> 01:16:51.560
circular systems on the
automobile and up in the air

01:16:51.560 --> 01:16:54.540
some strange piece
of technology.

01:16:54.540 --> 01:16:57.280
Next.

01:16:57.280 --> 01:17:01.450
Wright [INAUDIBLE] at the
same time was indulging his

01:17:01.450 --> 01:17:08.170
fantasies on the left
in a project for--

01:17:08.170 --> 01:17:14.980
I can't remember the date,
probably after the Depression

01:17:14.980 --> 01:17:20.080
years, the new Chicago life
insurance National Life

01:17:20.080 --> 01:17:24.730
Insurance Corporation
and this very small town

01:17:24.730 --> 01:17:28.780
in Bartlesville, Oklahoma
for the Price family,

01:17:28.780 --> 01:17:31.960
where as I said in
a previous class,

01:17:31.960 --> 01:17:34.600
we have the first
attempt in modern times,

01:17:34.600 --> 01:17:38.290
I think, to put offices and
housing on the same floor

01:17:38.290 --> 01:17:38.920
in a building.

01:17:42.060 --> 01:17:44.012
Next.

01:17:44.012 --> 01:17:56.000
Corbusier was so authoritarian
in his ambit of knowledge

01:17:56.000 --> 01:18:04.370
that he could depict the
greatest human establishment,

01:18:04.370 --> 01:18:08.870
the Ville [INAUDIBLE],,
the linear city,

01:18:08.870 --> 01:18:15.410
the agricultural
community, the journey

01:18:15.410 --> 01:18:19.530
of the sun for 24 hours.

01:18:19.530 --> 01:18:20.030
Next.

01:18:23.900 --> 01:18:26.270
In the drawing on the
section on the left,

01:18:26.270 --> 01:18:30.230
you have some of the key
elements of his building

01:18:30.230 --> 01:18:32.750
and also urbanism.

01:18:32.750 --> 01:18:35.750
The high, the sun on
the roof, the roof

01:18:35.750 --> 01:18:39.470
is given to physical culture.

01:18:39.470 --> 01:18:41.330
The center of the
building is given

01:18:41.330 --> 01:18:45.710
to the rue interieure, taken
just really from Fourier,

01:18:45.710 --> 01:18:49.040
but with no sexuality given.

01:18:49.040 --> 01:18:53.180
[INAUDIBLE] the building
itself lifted off

01:18:53.180 --> 01:18:58.100
the ground with vigorous
landscape [INAUDIBLE]..

01:19:00.700 --> 01:19:07.450
And this is one of these
great buildings in Algiers,

01:19:07.450 --> 01:19:10.990
the [INAUDIBLE]
building where there

01:19:10.990 --> 01:19:15.460
is a semblance to the
system on the left.

01:19:15.460 --> 01:19:15.960
Next.

01:19:19.270 --> 01:19:22.780
The first plan, a plan for
three million inhabitants,

01:19:22.780 --> 01:19:25.420
the center of which
would be the office

01:19:25.420 --> 01:19:31.760
environment for the capitalists,
very primitive ideas

01:19:31.760 --> 01:19:34.310
about vehicular transportation.

01:19:34.310 --> 01:19:39.405
But still, it was before the
Merritt Parkway was ever built.

01:19:39.405 --> 01:19:39.905
Next.

01:19:42.500 --> 01:19:50.690
The Voisin Plan, just
allocating his nausea

01:19:50.690 --> 01:19:53.600
for the 19th century street.

01:19:53.600 --> 01:19:57.080
This is an absolute
renunciation of what

01:19:57.080 --> 01:19:59.750
we call the DNA of Paris.

01:19:59.750 --> 01:20:10.210
[? Langier ?] said of making
a city, make it like a forest.

01:20:10.210 --> 01:20:13.120
There's something intrinsic
in the diagonal through which

01:20:13.120 --> 01:20:18.340
our friend [? Hartzband, ?]
of course, understood.

01:20:18.340 --> 01:20:22.630
Corbusier introduces
a new form of housing,

01:20:22.630 --> 01:20:26.620
a new control of the ground.

01:20:26.620 --> 01:20:30.430
Who controls all the
open space that is left?

01:20:30.430 --> 01:20:33.730
These great parks,
who maintains them?

01:20:36.700 --> 01:20:40.540
Is there any question that
this is an imposition which

01:20:40.540 --> 01:20:45.840
is tested on any grounds
amongst the people who

01:20:45.840 --> 01:20:47.670
are going live there?

01:20:47.670 --> 01:20:53.480
This is utopian in the sense
that it's a free interpretation

01:20:53.480 --> 01:20:55.460
of an alternative-- next--

01:20:55.460 --> 01:20:58.760
without taste.

01:20:58.760 --> 01:21:04.660
He was interested in the
machine and its capacity

01:21:04.660 --> 01:21:06.490
for creating linearity.

01:21:06.490 --> 01:21:13.270
This is not Henry Ford's
system of production,

01:21:13.270 --> 01:21:15.400
but a system of communication.

01:21:15.400 --> 01:21:19.840
On the lower slide on the
left is his proposition

01:21:19.840 --> 01:21:24.130
for Rio de Janeiro.

01:21:24.130 --> 01:21:27.710
He made a similar proposition
along with water--

01:21:27.710 --> 01:21:32.230
well, not Sao Paulo
is not on the water.

01:21:32.230 --> 01:21:37.090
Sorry, this is
Buenos Aires I think.

01:21:37.090 --> 01:21:42.990
I can't remember
everything, pretty.

01:21:42.990 --> 01:21:46.680
On the right his work, his work
with the [INAUDIBLE] Group,

01:21:46.680 --> 01:21:50.080
connecting all of
Europe linearly.

01:21:50.080 --> 01:21:50.580
Next.

01:21:53.810 --> 01:21:57.850
His Algiers proposal,
the Quartier de la Marine

01:21:57.850 --> 01:22:04.690
on the right side is replaced
by two towers facing France.

01:22:09.020 --> 01:22:12.860
The idea of inhabiting
the space under.

01:22:17.720 --> 01:22:20.750
What's going to happen to
all of the elevated highways

01:22:20.750 --> 01:22:21.410
in the world?

01:22:30.610 --> 01:22:32.560
Just about done.

